Newton's law of gravitation states that the gravitational force between any two <b>point objects</b>&nbsp;is<br><ul><li>Always and&nbsp;<b>attractive&nbsp;</b>force.</li><li>Proportional to the mass of each object.</li><li>Proportional to&nbsp;\(\frac{1}{r^2}\), where&nbsp;\(r\)&nbsp;is their distance apart.</li></ul>